crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a backdoor. It establishes persistence by copying itself to `/var/lock/kdumpflush` and uses `prctl` to masquerade as a legitimate system process (e.g., `/sbin/udevd -d`, `/sbin/auditd -n`). The malware opens a raw socket to sniff network traffic for trigger packets. Upon receiving a valid command, it can either spawn a reverse shell by executing `/bin/sh` and redirecting its I/O to a network socket, or manipulate `iptables` rules to redirect traffic.
